The Proposal: -

As per the above mentioned government decision, it has been approved to provide Shiv Bhojan thali at a discounted rate to the poor and needy people of the state. For this scheme, in the financial year 2025-26, an amount of Rs. A budgetary provision of 70.00 crores has been approved. Reference No. As per 03, the Department of Finance has released an amount of Rs. 21.00 crores has been made available. However, it is under the consideration of the government to disburse the amount to the offices of the Deputy Controller (Ration Allocation), Survey Food Distribution Officer and District Supply Officer.

Government Decision: - To provide Shiv Bhojan thali at subsidized rates to poor and needy persons, District Supply Officer, Food Distribution Officer B. Deputy Controller, Ration Allocation has been sanctioned a grant of Rs. Out of the 70.00 crore, the Department of Finance has allocated Rs. The 21.00 crore has been released.
The disbursement of the amount to the districts is being approved subject to the following conditions and conditions.

1. Subject to all the terms and conditions of the Government Decision and Circular referred to, the amount as mentioned in "Sub-Paper-A" shall be Rs. 921,00,00, 000 / - (literal amount Rs. 21 crore only) is being sanctioned to District Supply Officer, Food Distribution Officer and Deputy Controller Ration Allocation.
The grant should be spent for the same purpose for which it has been sanctioned. This amount cannot be used or diverted for any other purpose.

Accounts of expenditure from the above grants should be kept in the current account and the utility certificate of the payments made in that month after the payments from the treasury are made through your office in this regard should be submitted to the Accountant General's office and the government by the 15th of the next month after the standard and date-wise end of the month.

3. The District Collector (Drawing and Disbursement Officer in the office of District Purbatha Officer / Food Distribution Officer) at the district level is being authorised to draw the amount from the treasury as indicated in Co-Print-A and the Sub Divisional Office-wise Drawing and Disbursing Officer of Controller, Director of Ration Allocation, Civil Supplies is being authorised to draw the grant from the Office of Accounts Officer, Mumbai for Mumbai / Thane Ration Area.

4. It may be noted that since the receipt of the said grant, action should be taken in the next ten days from the receipt of the grant in strict compliance with all the rules of the Government, otherwise the grant would be withdrawn and distributed as per the requirement of other districts. Also, the Financial Adviser B Deputy Secretary will have full powers to redistribute the grant to the extent of the grant available as per the requirement of the other district.

5. The above subsidy shall be provided to the concerned institution every 15 days through online RTGS mode after taking into account the information of Shiv Bhojan App as directed earlier by the Government. Since the institutions are supposed to make payments online, appropriate action should be taken by obtaining the details of the back account of these institutions.

6. Expenditure for the purpose "Demand No. M-2, headings 2408 - Food, Storage and Warehousing, 01 - Food, 101 - Procurement and Supply, (03) Procurement, Distribution and Price Control, (03) (23) Shiv Bhojan Yojana (Programme), (24080772) 33 - Financing "to be sub-divided from the approved budgetary provision for the financial year 2025-26.
